# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration Report

## Summary
Vercel Web Analytics was **already installed and properly configured** in this project. The implementation follows the latest official Vercel documentation guidelines for Next.js App Router projects.

## Current Implementation Status

### ✅ Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
- **Status**: Already present in package.json dependencies
- **Action Taken**: Updated package-lock.json by running `npm install` to ensure all dependencies are properly resolved

### ✅ Analytics Component Integration  
- **Location**: `src/app/layout.tsx` (root layout)
- **Import**: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- **Usage**: `<Analytics />` component rendered inside the `<body>` tag
- **Framework**: Next.js App Router (using the correct `/next` import path)

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component is properly placed in the root layout file at `src/app/layout.tsx`:

```typescript
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";

export default async function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang={lang} suppressHydrationWarning>
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This implementation:
- ✅ Uses the correct Next.js App Router import (`@vercel/analytics/next`)
- ✅ Places the component at the root layout level for site-wide tracking
- ✅ Renders the component inside the `<body>` tag as recommended
- ✅ Follows the exact pattern from official Vercel documentation

